<h2 id="when-to-use-checkboxes">When to use checkboxes</h2>

<p>Use checkboxes to give users the ability to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>select multiple options from a list</li>
  <li>toggle an option on or off</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="when-not-to-use-a-checkbox">When not to use a checkbox</h2>

<p>If you want users to select just one option from a selection, for examples a yes or no answer, use the <a href="radio">radio</a> element.</p>

<h2 id="how-to-use-checkboxes">How to use checkboxes</h2>

<p>Checkboxes should be grouped together in a &lt;fieldset&gt; to help users understand they are related with a &lt;legend&gt; that describes the group clearly.</p>

<h3 id="accessibility">Accessibility</h3>

<p>To ensure checkboxes are accessible it is important that the input and label are connected so assisstive technologies can recognise they are connected.</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>    &lt;input id="post" name="post" type="checkbox" value="Post"&gt;
    &lt;label for="post"&gt;Post&lt;/label&gt;
</code></pre></div></div>

<h2 id="content-to-be-published">Content to be published</h2>

<ul>
  <li>Error handling with checkboxes</li>
  <li>Conditionally revealing content</li>
  <li>Checkbox hints</li>
</ul>

